JOHANNESBURG – Airlines Fly Safair and Airlink are planning a merger. The two airlines are set to apply for the approval at the Competition Commission on Tuesday. Despite being united under the Airlink brand, they will operate separately. Products, fleets and management of the companies will remain the same. READ: FlySafair R1 ticket frenzy Both companies have hailed the move describing it as one that will guarantee future growth and effectiveness and make air travel widely available across the country. eNCA